FBIS3-52722 "drnes005_j_94007" FBIS-NES-94-005 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Jan 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Death of 5 Military Personnel Announced JN0601181594 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 1200 GMT 6 Jan 94 JN0601181594 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] To the righteous soul will be said: O thou soul, in complete rest and satisfaction, come back thou to thy lord, well pleased thyself, and well-pleasing unto him. Enter thou, then, among my devotees. Yea, enter thou my heaven. [koranic verse] The Defense Ministry and the Armed Forces General Staff Command regret to announce the martyrdom of [name indistinct]; Major Salih Husayn; Maj. 'Ali 'Ali [surname indistinct]; Lieutenant Husni Muhammad Qa'id; Chief Warrant Officer [name indistinct]. They died on Tuesday, in the Province of [name indistinct] as a result of [word indistinct]. A military investigation committee has been set up to try to find the cause and motive behind this painful incident. As the Ministry announces the death of the martyrs and extends condolences to their families, it declares that it will remain committed to their (?families) and recognition of their role and (?practical) duty and their patriotic services to the Armed Forces. May the martyrs enjoy God's mercy and end up in his paradise, and may he grant their relatives patience and solace. We belong to God, and to him we return. It is to be recalled that [words indistinct] in the Lahaj Governorate, the bodies of the five martyrs were found in scattered places, four already dead. The fifth was admitted to the [word indistinct] military hospital, where he died of his wounds. Brother Staff Brigadier General Haytham Qasim Tahir, minister of defense, has set up an inquiry to investigate the incident and determine the identity of the culprits. [passage omitted]
